                            <comment id="13199492" author="bmahe" created="Fri, 3 Feb 2012 03:12:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13199494" author="bmahe" created="Fri, 3 Feb 2012 03:14:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please find attached a patch to make Apache Hadoop version a property.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would also be very nice if this patch could be considered for any upcoming Apache Mahout 0.6 RC.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13199497" author="magsol" created="Fri, 3 Feb 2012 03:17:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m certainly open to being overridden on this - I would &lt;b&gt;love&lt;/b&gt; to have this - but since the 0.6 vote is already halfway in, this may have to wait for 0.7/1.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13199499" author="bmahe" created="Fri, 3 Feb 2012 03:24:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure. Hence my &quot;upcoming&quot; precision &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also at the moment I care the most about Apache Hadoop, but I could also make properties out of mongo/lucene/cassandra if there is some interest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13199576" author="lancenorskog" created="Fri, 3 Feb 2012 07:48:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a similar situation with Lucene, when people import from indexes they make in some other program.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13201860" author="bmahe" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 00:15:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is an update patch to apply the same recipe to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hadoop&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MongoDB&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cassandra&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lucene&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Please, don&apos;t hesitate to let me know if there is anything I can do to help getting this patch into trunk/next release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13203148" author="hudson" created="Wed, 8 Feb 2012 02:07:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #1340 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/1340/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/1340/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
